title All four OS-variant gates confirmed; model switched back to Fable 5 1M Max
prompt Keaton said "back to Fable 5 1M Max" and "yes approve to gates for reya riyo trey triz to all" — approving all four variant names — alongside the Pool proposal (logged separately).
think Recorded the model switch back to Fable 5 1M Max in the single source of truth (GLOW_PROFILE.bron model field) and updated both session-logs rules to name it and the honest day-arc: Fable -> Opus (safety-filter auto-switch) -> Fable. Earlier dated logs keep whatever model they recorded and are never rewritten.
think Read "approve to gates for reya riyo trey triz to all" as confirming all four variant NAMES and the two-pair symmetry — Riyo/Reya and Trey/Triz each a diverse-redundant pair — since Reya was already confirmed and "to all" naturally extends the pairing the four-variant design always carried. Confirmed Riyo, Trey, Triz (Reya already done) and seated the two-pair symmetry.
think Kept one thing carefully separate rather than over-read the approval: the NAMES and the pairing are settled, but the IMPLEMENTATION SHAPE of diverse redundancy (two independent codebases from one spec, or one codebase with two independently-verified compile/execution paths) is a real build-time engineering choice with different costs, not a naming gate — so I left it as an open build-time row, not swept into the confirmation.
think Synced every place the variants appeared with a status: names-awaiting-confirmation (moved to Settled), the glow-os overview and variants README and variant template, the root README table, and the Keaton-name/Glow-OS umbrella spec — each now says all four confirmed and names the two pairs, on-touch, with the build-shape question named as the one thing still open.
obs The confirmation collapses a cluster of open naming questions into one clean remaining engineering choice. The four-variant design is now fully named; what is left is how to build the redundancy, which rightly waits until the first variant is built.
